Thank you Adriene!!  I have been following Yoga with Adrienne since 2011!  At age 64, a diagnosis of cancer (leiomyosarcoma), major pelvic surgery and radiation prevented me from attending my usual yoga classes for several weeks - which is when I found Adrienne.  Since then I have had three metastases - lung, rib, and now both lungs again - more surgery and more radiation (5” of 11th rib removed) and have continued to follow and NEED Adrienne, even when I did return to local classes.  I not only follow her 30 day journeys but choose many others in between as needed.   My doctors feel that yoga has helped my mind and body stay strong.  Without Adriene I would not have continued my yoga practices.  Now I am 75, and as todays mantra states…. I am strong.  Again, thank you Adriene!

this is crazy! i'm a really bad insomniac, but for the past week my sleep schedule has been alright, except for today when i woke up at 4 am restless. I had so much energy, but i was also so sleepy at the same time, so when i came to the mat, day 17 was snuggle! like, as if.

I'm a bit late, but that's okay. I'm trying to be kind to myself. Today was the firt time I recognized that I'm no longer getting anxouis about breathing deep and focosing on my breath. Years ago I started getting really heavy migrains and every time I tried to breath deep and at the same pace. On some point, every time I tried to focus on my breath I got light headed and scared, because I connected the breathing to the scary feeling of my migraines. Thanks to your practices, it got better and I did'nt even noticed until today! Thank you a lot!

I took a step back, rewinded the video, and made some necessary adjustments. I finished the practice feeling relieved and peaceful, truly grateful for this lesson. Thank you Adriene. Namaste!🙏💜

At the end of practice, sitting on my pillow and covered in my blanket, I got a flood of emotion hit me as I whispered “namaste” in response. I’ve been doing yoga with you for about 5-6 years now. The first couple of years, I did it everyday (sometimes twice a day!), just loving every moment. Over time, I gradually fell out, and would have a hard time keeping up with the 30 day journeys. This year, though, I have done everyday in a row—and sometimes even extra little practices. I find myself returning to the sense of strength, awareness, and love I had so enjoyed when I first began my practice with you. Thank you, Adriene. I so appreciate you ❤️
